  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Fast-track programs in Orthopaedic Surgery require early motion that can only be achieved by
      optimal pain management protocols. Multimodal analgesia protocols including local
      infiltration anesthesia (LIA) have obtained excellent results in fast-track programs
      involving Total Knee Arthroplasty but further research and data is needed in Total Hip
      Arthoplasty programs.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
